Although the order of the stream is乱序的 (out of order), the browser assembles the HTML document in the correct order.
@user22 Actually, you can reorder the document content without using JavaScript. However, if you want the server to do something, you cannot use the hash part of the URL; instead, you need to use query string parameters to inform the server which part you want to see first. As for reordering the page content, you have the following options:
1. Using CSS
2. Use a template with slots
